    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect loop bounds and memory access in dft1536/idft1536 functions\n\n### Summary\nThe `dft1536()` and `idft1536()` functions in `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c` contain incorrect loop bounds and output indexing that cause incorrect DFT computations and potential buffer overruns.\n\n### Issue Details\nWhen processing 1536-point DFT/IDFT operations, the functions were using a loop condition of `i<1024` instead of `i<512`, causing the butterfly operations to iterate 1024 times instead of the correct 512 times. Additionally, the output indexing was incorrect, using offsets of 1024 and 2048 instead of 512 and 1024.\n\nThis leads to:\n1. Incorrect DFT/IDFT results due to wrong number of butterfly operations\n2. Writing output data to incorrect memory locations\n3. Potential buffer overflows when accessing memory beyond the allocated output buffer\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Call either `dft1536()` or `idft1536()` with a 1536-point input signal\n2. Observe incorrect output values due to wrong loop bounds\n3. Potential crashes or memory corruption due to out-of-bounds memory writes\n\nThe functions should perform exactly 512 3-point butterfly operations for a 1536-point transform (1536 = 3 \u00d7 512), but currently perform 1024 operations, leading to incorrect results.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Corrected loop bounds from `i<1024` to `i<512` in both `dft1536()` and `idft1536()` functions\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Fixed output indexing from `(output+i),(output+1024+i),(output+2048+i)` to `(output+i),(output+512+i),(output+1024+i)` in both functions\n\n"
}